  "prompt": "How did Stitch Fix start?",
  "response": "Stitch Fix was founded in 2011 by Katrina Lake, who came up with the idea while she was a graduate student at Harvard Business School. The concept originated from her observation of the challenges many people faced in finding personalized clothing that suits their style without the hassle of shopping in stores. \n\nKatrina Lake aimed to create a service that combined personal styling with convenience by offering customers a subscription-based model. Users would fill out a detailed style profile online, indicating their preferences, sizes, and budget. Then, professional stylists would curate a selection of clothing and accessories tailored to the individual's tastes and send them to the customer\u2019s home. Customers could try on the items, keep what they liked, and send back what they didn't want.\n\nStitch Fix began as a simple idea but quickly grew in popularity. The company utilized data and algorithms to enhance the personalization of its service, allowing it to scale effectively. Over the years, Stitch Fix expanded its offerings to include a wider range of sizes and styles, targeting various demographics.\n\nThe company went public in 2017, further solidifying its status in the fashion and tech industries. Today, Stitch Fix is known for blending data science with personal styling, continuously evolving its model to meet customer needs.",
